  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6766 sitting directly between massive negative gamma walls at 6770/6765 (-12B/-10.4B) and just below the max positive gamma at 6780 (+7.5B), dealers are in active selling mode as they hedge short gamma positions. The PIN regime should provide mean-reversion support, but the concentration of negative gamma below current levels means any dip toward 6760 will trigger amplified dealer buying that could spark a sharp bounce back toward 6780-6800. Key inflection point is 6770 - a break below activates the largest negative gamma wall and forces heavy dealer buying, while a push above 6780 flips dealers to selling mode against positive gamma.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile whipsaw action between 6760-6780 with strong magnetic pull toward the 6770-6780 range.",
